HEADWORD: Solicitation
<hw>So*lic`i*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sollicitation</ets>, or L. <ets>sollicitatio</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of soliciting; earnest request; persistent
asking; importunity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excitement; invitation; <as>as, the
<ex>solicitation</ex> of the senses</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solicitor</ent>⟦br⟧
